                            <comment id="14697642" author="hvanhovell" created="Fri, 14 Aug 2015 19:49:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There is a small bug in the Python code: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/python/pyspark/sql/window.py#L67&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/python/pyspark/sql/window.py#L67&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is calling &lt;tt&gt;partitionBy&lt;/tt&gt; instead of &lt;tt&gt;orderBy&lt;/tt&gt;. I never work with Python, and I have never build Spark with Python; so I don&apos;t think it the best idea to start my journey into the world of Python this way.&lt;/p&gt;

